    "notes": "Week 6 Day 7 of Talk 4 (Week 2 of 2, Final Day of Talk 4). Reflection & Integration focus: Full synthesis of the entire 2-week talk on Practical Thought About Practical Thought? Core frameworks: 5-Notion Framework (Simplify, Numerical Fluency, Invert, Study Basics, Seek Lollapalooza), Lollapalooza Effects (combinatorial power), Meta-Cognition Structure (thinking about thinking). 5 case snapshots - Coca-Cola's 140-year rise (applied all 5 notions for lollapalooza), TikTok's explosive growth (combined algorithmic personalization, social proof, variable rewards, dopamine loops, low-friction), PM who optimized wrong metric (man with a hammer syndrome, single-model thinking), Berkshire's GEICO acquisition (applied multidisciplinary thinking across economics, psychology, finance), Quibi's $1.75B failure (violated simplification, numerical fluency, inversion, elementary wisdom, lollapalooza). Integration exercise: Create Decision SOP using 5-notion framework. 5 reflection questions. Personal latticework update: ~15 models after 4 talks. Key takeaway: You don't need to be brilliant, just consistently not stupid—apply elementary wisdom multidisciplinary. Commitment: Create Decision SOP using 5-notion framework (one page, 15 min). Talk 4 complete. Next: Talk 5 (The Need for More Multidisciplinary Skills) starts Week 7 Day 1 (May 3). Message delivered successfully."
